Title: Cache CORS Preflight Requests
Description: Almost all applications are using CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) to allow the client to access the resources from the server. When the client sends a request to the server, the server will respond with the Access-Control-Allow-Origin header to allow the client to access the resources.
